The wife of a Detroit-area soccer referee filed a $ 51 million lawsuit Friday against a hot-headed player who is in prison for throwing a punch that killed her husband during a game last summer .
The figure represents $ 1 million for each of the 51 additional years that John Bieniewicz , 44 , could have lived .
Kristen Kristen of Westland , the representative of her husband 's estate , is suing Bassel Saad , along the team and the soccer league .
The lawsuit is in the Michigan United Soccer League .